    {%- comment -%}
      Article hero LCP preload 2026-05-04 (issue 9hw). GA4 RUM showed
      40–88% poor LCP on hair-education blog articles. The hero snippet
      was loading="lazy" by default. Adding eager:true on the render call
      (sections/article.liquid) adds fetchpriority=high, but the browser
      still discovers the image late (after CSS/JS preload finishes).
      This <link rel=preload> lets the browser queue the WebP fetch
      during initial HTML parse — the browser preload scanner picks it
      up before render-blocking resources finish.
      Gated on request.page_type == 'article' + article.image so it only
      fires on blog article pages that actually have a hero image.
      imagesrcset/imagesizes are the correct attributes for preloading
      responsive images (not srcset/sizes which are for <img>/<source>).
    {%- endcomment -%}
    {%- if request.page_type == 'article' and article.image -%}
      <link
        rel="preload"
        as="image"
        href="{{ article.image | image_url: width: 900, format: 'webp' }}"
        imagesrcset="{%- if article.image.width >= 540 -%}{{ article.image | image_url: width: 540, format: 'webp' }} 540w,{%- endif -%}
          {%- if article.image.width >= 900 -%}{{ article.image | image_url: width: 900, format: 'webp' }} 900w,{%- endif -%}
          {%- if article.image.width >= 1400 -%}{{ article.image | image_url: width: 1400, format: 'webp' }} 1400w,{%- endif -%}
          {%- if article.image.width >= 1800 -%}{{ article.image | image_url: width: 1800, format: 'webp' }} 1800w{%- endif -%}"
        imagesizes="100vw"
        type="image/webp">
    {%- endif -%}

    {%- comment -%}
      First-body-image LCP preload (bd iy4m, 2026-05-16). The 9hw preload
      above covers article.image, but field audit (2026-05-16) showed many
      high-traffic articles have a blank article.image OR have
      section.settings.blog_show_featured_image = false → the hero block at
      sections/article.liquid:27-39 does NOT render. In that case the actual
      LCP is the FIRST body <img>, which article-content-with-img-dims:170-184
      (issue 7tq) marks fetchpriority="high" + loading="eager" — but no
      preload is issued, so the LCP image loads cold from the post-CSS
      critical path.

      Fix: extract the first <img src=> from article.content and emit a
      preload. Liquid has no regex; uses split chains:
        article.content → split '<img ' → [1] → split '>' → first
                       → split 'src="' → [1] → split '"' → first.

      Verified pre-fix curl audit on three top-offending articles:
        salon-hair-color-vs-box-dye-...:    hero block missing, 0 preloads.
        before-and-after-purple-shampoo:    hero block missing, 0 preloads.
        purple-vs-blue-shampoo-philippines: hero block missing, 0 preloads.
      Each has an eager body img that loads cold — this preload covers them.

      Browser handles the case where article.image preload also fires: both
      preloads are queued; whichever the page actually renders as LCP wins
      the race. No harm from over-preloading by ~1 image; it's a known LCP
      optimisation pattern (Lighthouse "preload LCP image" suggestion).
    {%- endcomment -%}
    {%- if request.page_type == 'article' -%}
      {%- comment -%}
        Normalise article.content so the extraction is robust to whitespace
        variations in the rich-text editor's output. Two-step normalisation:
          1. Replace `<img` with `<img ` (force trailing space).
          2. Split on '<img ' — chunks[1] is everything after the first <img.
        Then split on 'src="' (with double-quote fallback to single-quote)
        to extract the src URL. Skip if URL doesn't look like a valid path.
      {%- endcomment -%}
      {%- assign _normalised = article.content | default: '' | replace: '<img', '<img ' -%}
      {%- assign _body_chunks = _normalised | split: '<img ' -%}
      {%- assign _first_body_img_url = '' -%}
      {%- if _body_chunks.size > 1 -%}
        {%- assign _first_img_attrs = _body_chunks[1] | split: '>' | first -%}
        {%- assign _src_segments_dq = _first_img_attrs | split: 'src="' -%}
        {%- if _src_segments_dq.size > 1 -%}
          {%- assign _first_body_img_url = _src_segments_dq[1] | split: '"' | first -%}
        {%- else -%}
          {%- assign _src_segments_sq = _first_img_attrs | split: "src='" -%}
          {%- if _src_segments_sq.size > 1 -%}
            {%- assign _first_body_img_url = _src_segments_sq[1] | split: "'" | first -%}
          {%- endif -%}
        {%- endif -%}
      {%- endif -%}
      {%- if _first_body_img_url and _first_body_img_url != '' and _first_body_img_url contains '/' -%}
        <link rel="preload" as="image" href="{{ _first_body_img_url }}" fetchpriority="high">
      {%- endif -%}
    {%- endif -%}

