    {%- endcomment -%}
    {%- comment -%}
      Drawer-toggle click intercept (added 2026-04-28; rewritten 2026-04-28
      after a Cloudflare-bot-challenge regression).

      Background: header cart icon and other [data-drawer-toggle] buttons
      have BOTH href={routes.cart_url} (link fallback) AND a click handler
      bound by deferred theme.js that does preventDefault and opens the
      drawer. On fast pages — or when theme.js fails to fully load (e.g.,
      after a Cloudflare bot-detection challenge throttles the user's IP) —
      the click falls through to link navigation and the user lands on the
      standalone /cart page instead of seeing the drawer.

      First version (queue + replay on DOMContentLoaded) caused a worse
      regression: the synthetic queued.click() replay needed theme.js's
      button-level handler to be bound by replay-time. If theme.js had
      not bound (Cloudflare-induced loading delay/failure), the replayed
      click bubbled to the link href and navigated.

      This version is self-contained: capture-phase listener at document
      level intercepts every [data-drawer-toggle] click, preventDefault +
      stopImmediatePropagation (suppresses theme.js's redundant button-
      level handler), and dispatches theme:drawer:toggle DIRECTLY on the
      matched drawer element. The Drawer instance's listener (bound in
      theme.js's drawer constructor at section-load time) handles toggle.

      Works whether or not theme.js's connectToggle bound its own click
      handler — only depends on the Drawer instance existing in DOM and
      its toggle listener being attached. If theme.js fails entirely
      (no Drawer instance), click does nothing — better than wrong /cart
      navigation. ~450 bytes inline cost, runs before first paint.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <script>
      (function () {
        document.addEventListener('click', function (e) {
          var btn = e.target.closest && e.target.closest('[data-drawer-toggle]');
          if (!btn) return;
          var key = btn.getAttribute('data-drawer-toggle');
          var drawer = document.querySelector('[data-drawer="' + key + '"]');
          if (!drawer) return; // no drawer in DOM, let link fallback navigate
          e.preventDefault();
          e.stopImmediatePropagation();
          drawer.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('theme:drawer:toggle', { bubbles: false }));
        }, true);
      })();
    </script>
    {%- comment -%}
      RUM removed 2026-04-28 PM — was a duplicate of the existing
      snippets/web-vitals-reporter.liquid (shipped 2 days earlier in
      commit 367f920 — uses Google's official web-vitals.js v4
      attribution build with TTFB + metric_rating + debug_target +
      navigation_type, richer than this inline block).

      The existing reporter is rendered at theme.liquid line ~874
      ({% render 'web-vitals-reporter' %}) and pushes events to GTM
      as event=LCP|CLS|INP|FCP|TTFB (each metric its own event)
      with params: value, metric_id, metric_value, metric_delta,
      metric_rating, metric_navigation_type, debug_target, page_path.

      My duplicate inline reporter would have double-counted every
      vital event in GA4. Removing now. The js_error tracking below
      is genuinely new (existing reporter doesn't track JS errors),
      so kept.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    {%- comment -%}
      JS error tracking — added 2026-04-28.

      Captures uncaught exceptions and unhandled promise rejections,
      pushes to window.dataLayer for GTM forwarding to GA4. Pairs with
      the RUM reporter above — together: WHEN errors happen + how
      they correlate with web-vitals degradation.

      Why inline in head: error listeners must be installed BEFORE any
      script can throw. An external file would miss errors from the
      deferred bundle's first-frame execution.

      Throttled to max 10 errors per session to avoid:
        - Flooding GA4 quota (custom events have daily caps)
        - Throttling shopper bandwidth on a runaway error loop
        - Doxxing the error to GA4 hundreds of times in one session

      Cost: ~500 bytes inline. Only activates on actual errors.

      Receives in GTM:
        event: hairmnl_js_error  (prefixed to avoid collision with Elevar's own js_error push)
        error_message: error.message (truncated 200 chars)
        error_source: filename:line:col (truncated 100 chars)
        error_type: 'error' | 'rejection'

      GA4-side event name is still 'js_error' (set in GTM tag eventName).
      The dataLayer event name was renamed from js_error → hairmnl_js_error
      on 2026-05-02 because Elevar's old install also pushes {event:'js_error'}
      with its own field names — that collision fired our GTM trigger but our
      DLVs (reading error_type etc.) returned undefined for Elevar's events,
      producing ~30k (not set) hits/7d. GTM trigger updated to match.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    {%- comment -%}
      A/B testing framework — added 2026-04-28.

      Foundation for theme-side experiments. Currently NO TESTS DEFINED;
      add entries to the `TESTS` object below to start an experiment.

      How a test works:
        1. Add a key to TESTS with weights (typically 50/50 split):
             TESTS = {
               'cart-bar-style': { weights: { A: 50, B: 50 } }
             };
        2. Variant is assigned ONCE per shopper, persisted in cookie
           (_ab_<testId>) for 90 days, stable across pages and sessions.
        3. Variant is added as a CSS class on <html>:
             html.ab-cart-bar-style-A { ... A styling ... }
             html.ab-cart-bar-style-B { ... B styling ... }
           (or check via JS: document.documentElement.classList.contains(...))
        4. Variant is pushed to window.dataLayer:
             { event: 'ab_test', ab_test_id, ab_variant }
           GTM forwards to GA4 as a custom event for segmentation.

      QA override: append ?_ab=A or ?_ab=B to any URL to force a variant
      (one URL param applies to all active tests — useful for spot checks,
      not for production traffic). Override does NOT persist in cookie.

      Cost: ~700 bytes inline. Zero overhead when TESTS is empty (default).
      Cookie write only on first assignment per test.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <script>
      (function () {
        var TESTS = {
          // Add experiments here. Example:
          // 'cart-bar-style': { weights: { A: 50, B: 50 } },
        };
        if (Object.keys(TESTS).length === 0) return;
        var dl = (window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || []);
        function getVariant(id, weights) {
          var urlOverride = new URLSearchParams(location.search).get('_ab');
          if (urlOverride) return urlOverride;
          var key = '_ab_' + id;
          var m = document.cookie.match(new RegExp('(^|;\\s*)' + key + '=([^;]+)'));
          if (m) return m[2];
          var total = 0;
          for (var k in weights) total += weights[k];
          var rand = Math.random() * total, sum = 0, variant = Object.keys(weights)[0];
          for (var k2 in weights) { sum += weights[k2]; if (rand < sum) { variant = k2; break; } }
          document.cookie = key + '=' + variant + ';path=/;max-age=' + (90 * 24 * 3600);
          return variant;
        }
        for (var id in TESTS) {
          var v = getVariant(id, TESTS[id].weights);
          document.documentElement.classList.add('ab-' + id + '-' + v);
          dl.push({ event: 'ab_test', ab_test_id: id, ab_variant: v });
        }
      })();
    </script>
    <script>
      (function () {
        var dl = (window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || []);
        var errorCount = 0;
        var MAX_ERRORS = 10;
        function send(type, message, source) {
          if (errorCount >= MAX_ERRORS) return;
          errorCount++;
          dl.push({
            event: 'hairmnl_js_error',
            error_type: type,
            error_message: String(message || '').slice(0, 200),
            error_source: String(source || '').slice(0, 100)
          });
        }
        addEventListener('error', function (e) {
          var src = (e.filename || '') + ':' + (e.lineno || 0) + ':' + (e.colno || 0);
          // p8j 2026-05-10: prefer e.error.name (TypeError, ReferenceError, SyntaxError, etc.)
          // for first-party errors. Cross-origin errors have e.error redacted to null by the
          // browser — those fall back to the literal "error" bucket. Promise rejections stay
          // categorical via the unhandledrejection handler below.
          var t = (e.error && e.error.name) ? e.error.name : 'error';
          send(t, e.message, src);
        }, { capture: true });
        addEventListener('unhandledrejection', function (e) {
          var msg = e.reason && (e.reason.message || e.reason.toString()) || 'unknown rejection';
          var src = e.reason && e.reason.stack ? e.reason.stack.split('\n')[1] || '' : '';
          send('rejection', msg, src.trim());
        });
      })();
    </script>
